Sentencas: Joining of NiO-YSZ cermet with 316 stainless steel was carried out using B-Ni3 brazing alloy (4.5 wt% Si, 3.2 wt% B, 0.06 wt% C, 0.02 wt% P, Ni-balance, m.p. 982-1038 degrees C) to realize reliable sealing of the NiO-YSZ cermet anode/316 stainless steel interconnect structure in a SOFC.
Titulo: Interfacial morphologies between NiO-YSZ fuel electrode/316 stainless steel as the interconnect material and B-Ni3 brazing alloy in a solid oxide fuel cell system

Sentencas: In the present research, interfacial (chemical) reactions during brazing at the NiO-YSZ/316 stainless steel interconnect were promoted by either of the two processing methods, (a) addition of an electroless nickel-plate to NiO-YSZ cermet as a coating or (b) deposition of titanium layer onto NiO-YSZ cermet by magnetron plasma sputtering method, with relevant process variables and procedures optimized during either of the pre-processing.
Titulo: Interfacial morphologies between NiO-YSZ fuel electrode/316 stainless steel as the interconnect material and B-Ni3 brazing alloy in a solid oxide fuel cell system

Sentencas: Brazing was performed in a cold-wall vacuum furnace at 1080 degrees C under vacuum level of 10(-3) Torr.
Titulo: Interfacial morphologies between NiO-YSZ fuel electrode/316 stainless steel as the interconnect material and B-Ni3 brazing alloy in a solid oxide fuel cell system

Sentencas: Post-brazing examination of interfacial morphologies between NiO-YSZ cermet and 316 stainless steel was made using SEM and EDS.
Titulo: Interfacial morphologies between NiO-YSZ fuel electrode/316 stainless steel as the interconnect material and B-Ni3 brazing alloy in a solid oxide fuel cell system

Sentencas: The results indicate that B-Ni3 brazing filler alloy was fused fully during brazing and continuous interfacial layer formation significantly depended on the method of pre-coating NiO-YSZ cermet.
Titulo: Interfacial morphologies between NiO-YSZ fuel electrode/316 stainless steel as the interconnect material and B-Ni3 brazing alloy in a solid oxide fuel cell system

Sentencas: The inter-diffusion of elements was possibly promoted by titanium-deposition which reduced the diffusion reaction thickness of the interfacial area to less than 16 mu m compared to 180 mu m for electroless nickel-deposited NiO-YSZ cermet.
Titulo: Interfacial morphologies between NiO-YSZ fuel electrode/316 stainless steel as the interconnect material and B-Ni3 brazing alloy in a solid oxide fuel cell system
